TERMINAL COMMANDS :-
# Update and upgrade system
--> sudo apt-get update
--> sudo apt-get upgrade -y

# Install Python 3 and pip (if not installed)
--> sudo apt-get install python3 python3-pip -y

# Install RPi.GPIO library
--> sudo pip3 install RPi.GPIO

# Install LCD library
--> sudo pip3 install RPLCD

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CONNECTIONS TABLE:-
| LCD Pin   | Function        | Raspberry Pi GPIO Pin (BCM) | Physical Pin No. |
| --------- | --------------- | --------------------------- | ---------------- |
| 1 (VSS)   | GND             | GND                         | 6                |
| 2 (VDD)   | +5V             | 5V                          | 2                |
| 3 (V0)    | Contrast        | Potentiometer middle pin    | -                |
| 4 (RS)    | Register Select | GPIO 26                     | 37               |
| 5 (RW)    | Read/Write      | GND                         | 6                |
| 6 (E)     | Enable          | GPIO 19                     | 35               |
| 11 (D4)   | Data Bit 4      | GPIO 13                     | 33               |
| 12 (D5)   | Data Bit 5      | GPIO 6                      | 31               |
| 13 (D6)   | Data Bit 6      | GPIO 5                      | 29               |
| 14 (D7)   | Data Bit 7      | GPIO 11                     | 23               |
| 15 (LED+) | Backlight +5V   | 5V through 220Î© resistor    | 2                |
| 16 (LED-) | Backlight GND   | GND                         | 6                |

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

CODE:-

import RPi.GPIO as GPIO
from RPLCD import CharLCD
from time import sleep

# LCD setup (4-bit mode)
lcd = CharLCD(numbering_mode=GPIO.BCM,
              cols=16, rows=2,
              pin_rs=26, pin_e=19,
              pins_data=[13, 6, 5, 11])

try:
    lcd.clear()
    lcd.write_string("Hello World!")
    sleep(2)
    lcd.clear()
    lcd.write_string("Raspberry Pi 3")
    lcd.crlf()  # Move to next line
    lcd.write_string("16x2 LCD Test")
    sleep(5)
finally:
    lcd.clear()
    GPIO.cleanup()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
